main event: A civilian reported observing a bright, luminous object moving rapidly across the night sky in Roswell, New Mexico on March 8, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as round or oval-shaped, approximately 40-50 feet in diameter, and emitting a pulsating glow.
The object was observed for approximately 30 seconds before disappearing from view.
The witness immediately reported the sighting to the local police department, who in turn notified the nearest Air Force base.
The case remains classified as 'Unidentified' due to the lack of any conclusive explanation for the observed phenomenon.
The report mentions a 35mm slide taken at Roswell depicting an unidentified metallic object, but the slide was evaluated and determined to be likely caused by a processing chemical on the film.
sighted object: a bright, luminous, round or oval-shaped object approximately 40-50 feet in diameter
photographs: yes, a 35mm slide was taken but determined to be inconclusive
